data.content:
## What Breaks in .NET 11

In .NET 11 / EF Core 11, the **sync-over-async opt-in for the Cosmos DB provider is removed**. All synchronous LINQ operators (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`) and `SaveChanges()` now throw `InvalidOperationException` at runtime.

The Cosmos DB SDK is inherently async-only, and EF Core 11 no longer bridges that gap — even with configuration.

## Fix: migrate to async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key changes:**
1. Return `Task<T>` / `Task` instead of sync types
2. Replace `ToList()` → `ToListAsync()`, `First()` → `FirstAsync()`, `Count()` → `CountAsync()`, `SaveChanges()` → `SaveChangesAsync()`
3. Propagate `async/await` up through your call chain (controllers, services, etc.)

You can also remove the old `EnableSyncOverAsync()` (or equivalent) call from your `DbContext` configuration — it's no longer recognized.
